1
00:00:05,625 --> 00:00:06,999
Have you considered
just once that Dad

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,124
is not the bloke
you think he is?

3
00:00:08,125 --> 00:00:09,332
He's a selfish prick.

4
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:10,541
They wanted us
out of the picture.

5
00:00:10,542 --> 00:00:11,624
Who wanted us out
of the picture?

6
00:00:11,625 --> 00:00:12,708
Albert, Lily.

7
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:17,832
- Where's the gold?!
- It's in the wheelbarrow.

8
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:19,249
Where's my gold, boy?

9
00:00:19,250 --> 00:00:20,417
Bob Fink's got it.

10
00:00:21,625 --> 00:00:22,791
Okay, Charlie.

11
00:00:22,792 --> 00:00:24,374
I want to see her.

12
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:25,666
They were supposed to kill you

13
00:00:25,667 --> 00:00:28,957
in Vic Hill's lockup
15 years ago.

14
00:00:28,958 --> 00:00:30,541
You were in on that?

15
00:00:30,542 --> 00:00:33,292
We all have to go a little
off peace at times.

16
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:39,749
Yes, sir.

17
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,750
The truck is on its way.

18
00:00:50,208 --> 00:00:52,457
Hello, hello,
my little Grim Reaper.

19
00:00:52,458 --> 00:00:54,207
You still trucking, baby?

20
00:00:54,208 --> 00:00:56,166
<i>How long until
your heavy-metal steed</i>

21
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:57,999
<i>slams into my throbbing
mosh pit?</i>

22
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,917
Should be clocked out by 2:00.

23
00:01:05,917 --> 00:01:07,625
Right, let's be having ya.

24
00:01:09,167 --> 00:01:11,042
No, you bloody well don't.

25
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,417
We've rung the bell.

26
00:01:57,042 --> 00:02:00,208
I warned you, Bobby-Boy.
Now look at ya.

27
00:02:01,208 --> 00:02:02,583
Right ol' mess.

28
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:06,249
Right, we got 30 hours
to the exchange.

29
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:08,332
Got a safe house
on Rivington Street

30
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:09,832
where we can stash it.

31
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:12,166
No.

32
00:02:12,167 --> 00:02:13,666
Take it to Elm Lodge.

33
00:02:13,667 --> 00:02:16,166
Bit close to home, sir.

34
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:18,832
I don't intend to let this
out of my sight, Dwyer.

35
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,499
Call Peters.

36
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:22,749
Have him meet us there
with the rest of the squad.

37
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,082
Load the gold into the van.

38
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:29,250
And if you ask Windrush nicely,
he might lend a hand.

39
00:02:32,875 --> 00:02:34,333
Well?

40
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:55,000
Keys, keys, keys, keys, keys.

41
00:02:58,875 --> 00:03:00,375
God.

42
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:28,874
Come on, let's go.
Come on, come on, boy.

43
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:31,000
Come on. Good boy.

44
00:04:05,917 --> 00:04:07,707
Vic.

45
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:09,249
Albert.

46
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,000
Lotti.

47
00:04:12,042 --> 00:04:13,122
What the hell's going on?

48
00:04:14,917 --> 00:04:16,332
Vic?
Family meeting, everyone out.

49
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:17,832
- Stay.
- Get out!

50
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,166
Stay! They've been more family

51
00:04:19,167 --> 00:04:20,957
than you have
these past few years.

52
00:04:20,958 --> 00:04:22,832
All right, I'll tell you
what happened.

53
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:26,582
Your son lost my gold
to Bob Fink, all of it!

54
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:27,916
Your gold?

55
00:04:27,917 --> 00:04:29,166
You had it for all of
about an hour

56
00:04:29,167 --> 00:04:31,249
15 years ago
the night you lost it.

57
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,791
- I was sold out.
- Yeah, by Bob Fink.

58
00:04:32,792 --> 00:04:34,332
How did we not see
that one coming?

59
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:36,666
That was then and this is now,
and now it's you!

60
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:39,207
You're the snake
in the grass, my own son.

61
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:42,041
You lied to me! Both of ya!

62
00:04:42,042 --> 00:04:43,374
Your father and your husband.

63
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:46,332
Father, that's debatable,
isn't it?

64
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:48,457
I try my best for you, boy.

65
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:50,499
Being a bank robber
and a responsible parent

66
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,166
weren't exactly
compatible occupations.

67
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:53,916
Who said you had to be
a bank robber?

68
00:04:53,917 --> 00:04:55,499
I wouldn't have cared if you
were a plumber or a pen pusher.

69
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:59,374
I was not meant to stick
my head under a sink

70
00:04:59,375 --> 00:05:01,374
or rot behind a desk!

71
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:03,999
And neither were you.
That is not the Hill way.

72
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,582
Hill way? Do me a favor.

73
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:07,916
We have been hanging on
by a thread

74
00:05:07,917 --> 00:05:08,999
as long as I can remember!

75
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,999
That is enough, the pair of you!

76
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,124
You are so blind.

77
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:18,416
So desperate to dish out
the blame.

78
00:05:18,417 --> 00:05:20,374
You are both
as obsessed as each other,

79
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:22,375
two peas from the same pod.

80
00:05:24,667 --> 00:05:27,374
Now, this bloody gold has taken

81
00:05:27,375 --> 00:05:29,542
its pound of flesh
from all of us.

82
00:05:31,417 --> 00:05:33,500
It's all of us, not just you.

83
00:05:35,375 --> 00:05:37,249
I'm glad it's gone.
Fink's welcome to it.

84
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:38,832
It can bury him the same way
it's buried

85
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:41,292
everybody else
who's had it in their hands.

86
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:48,457
It's late. We're all exhausted.

87
00:05:48,458 --> 00:05:49,583
Get some sleep.

88
00:05:51,583 --> 00:05:53,958
Everybody stays here tonight.

89
00:06:10,917 --> 00:06:12,667
What do you want, Vic?

90
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:15,083
My wife.

91
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,957
Fifteen years a long time
for a stag

92
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:23,874
to be estranged from his doe.

93
00:06:23,875 --> 00:06:25,707
The only loving embrace
you're gonna get tonight

94
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:26,999
is from the cushion of the sofa.

95
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,875
Well, I didn't mean it
like that, Lil.

96
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:33,458
I just... wanted to talk.

97
00:06:36,167 --> 00:06:38,082
- Well?
- Would you have preferred it

98
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:39,791
if I was a civilian, Lil,

99
00:06:39,792 --> 00:06:42,457
stuck behind a desk every day?

100
00:06:42,458 --> 00:06:44,457
Me wearing a tie.

101
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:46,332
You packing me cheese
and chutney sandwiches

102
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:49,499
every day for lunch,
would that have made you happy?

103
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,499
I knew who you were
when we tied the knot

104
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:54,499
and I signed up to it,
all of it.

105
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,500
And God knows
I've always fancied you.

106
00:06:57,917 --> 00:06:59,916
Sometimes I wish I didn't.

107
00:06:59,917 --> 00:07:02,333
Would've made all these
past years a lot more bearable.

108
00:07:04,042 --> 00:07:07,167
It's not me that you need
to worry about, it's your son.

109
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:10,666
He needs a father who loves him,

110
00:07:10,667 --> 00:07:14,249
who, more importantly,
trusts him.

111
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:17,250
You know, he's grown up into
a smart young man, your Albert.

112
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:21,833
I just hope you take the time
to get to know him.

113
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:34,666
You used to be a bit of
a footballer back in the day.

114
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:37,166
- You still play a bit?
- Why?

115
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:38,916
You fancy a kick about,
Hate 'Em?

116
00:07:38,917 --> 00:07:41,541
You know, your old man used
to drive me mad in the nick.

117
00:07:41,542 --> 00:07:44,291
Spun me the same story
over and over again

118
00:07:44,292 --> 00:07:46,166
about how you scored
the winning goal

119
00:07:46,167 --> 00:07:48,374
on some poxy
little league cup final.

120
00:07:48,375 --> 00:07:50,166
I'm surprised he even
remembered that.

121
00:07:50,167 --> 00:07:52,167
I never heard the end of it.

122
00:07:54,417 --> 00:07:56,291
The score was 1-1.

123
00:07:56,292 --> 00:07:58,166
It was the 89th minute.

124
00:07:58,167 --> 00:08:00,666
My Albert through on goal.

125
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:03,124
Legs pumping like a pair
of pistons.

126
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:04,624
Two massive defenders

127
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,999
descending down on him
from either side.

128
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,666
He drops his shoulder.

129
00:08:08,667 --> 00:08:10,791
Shells the first one like
a monkey nut.

130
00:08:10,792 --> 00:08:13,082
Second one got twisted
like a pretzel.

131
00:08:13,083 --> 00:08:15,082
Then it was my boy.

132
00:08:15,083 --> 00:08:16,832
One on one with the keeper.

133
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,082
The keeper's come out,
spread himself like an octopus,

134
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:21,082
all arms and legs.

135
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:22,916
My Albert stood his ground.

136
00:08:22,917 --> 00:08:24,832
Spun that kid like a tornado.

137
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,624
Smashed the back of that net.

138
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:28,875
Yes, get in there!

139
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:34,042
You know, I thought
I was gonna miss that?

140
00:08:40,125 --> 00:08:41,457
Your dad didn't.

141
00:08:41,458 --> 00:08:43,832
He always knew
you was gonna score.

142
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:46,375
Never doubted you for a minute.

143
00:08:49,208 --> 00:08:51,374
Anyway, look, I'm knackered.

144
00:08:51,375 --> 00:08:53,542
I'm gonna go
and get my head down.

145
00:08:54,917 --> 00:08:56,875
Good night, kid.

146
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:09,042
Back of the net.

147
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:23,833
Scoot.

148
00:09:25,292 --> 00:09:27,332
Wake me up in five.

149
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,333
I need to go and find the guys.

150
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:57,750
Charlie!

151
00:10:58,917 --> 00:11:00,332
- Charlie.
- Morning.

152
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:02,667
Morning. Come in.
The gang's in there.

153
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:05,499
Come here.

154
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:06,666
Where have you been?

155
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:08,999
Let me see.

156
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,332
I was kidnapped.

157
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:11,749
Handcuffed to a radiator.

158
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:13,457
Beaten to a pulp,
stuck in a closet,

159
00:11:13,458 --> 00:11:15,041
then witness to a brutal murder.

160
00:11:15,042 --> 00:11:16,457
You, been hitting

161
00:11:16,458 --> 00:11:17,874
the old gin and mushrooms
again, mate?

162
00:11:17,875 --> 00:11:19,999
Those days are behind me,
Billy-Boy.

163
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,416
I'm a new man.

164
00:11:21,417 --> 00:11:23,666
- Who's this?
- This is Scooter.

165
00:11:23,667 --> 00:11:27,082
I adopted him.

166
00:11:27,083 --> 00:11:29,666
God, what happened? Someone die?

167
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:31,500
Yeah, actually,
quite a few people.

168
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:35,667
We lost the gold, Charlie.

169
00:11:37,083 --> 00:11:38,791
Fink's got it. We're done.

170
00:11:38,792 --> 00:11:41,749
Yeah, well, actually,
Fink doesn't have it.

171
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:42,999
He's dead.

172
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,624
What do you mean... Fink's dead?

173
00:11:45,625 --> 00:11:48,249
Yeah, with Fink's brains
splattered across the rug,

174
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:51,374
off skipped
Chief Superintendent Jones

175
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:53,332
to Elm Lodge with our bounty.

176
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:55,624
Do you know this Jones
character, Hate 'Em?

177
00:11:55,625 --> 00:11:56,874
Yeah, he was a bent copper

178
00:11:56,875 --> 00:11:58,957
on the beat
from back in the day.

179
00:11:58,958 --> 00:12:00,832
Must have bullied his way
up the ladder.

180
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:03,666
And he said 30 hours
to this exchange, right?

181
00:12:03,667 --> 00:12:05,166
So he's gonna off-load the gold

182
00:12:05,167 --> 00:12:06,999
early tomorrow morning
to his client.

183
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,457
So that gives us enough time
to track him down, right?

184
00:12:09,458 --> 00:12:12,624
We are not going through
all this again.

185
00:12:12,625 --> 00:12:16,249
We are not going after the gold.

186
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:17,666
Now, I said it would kill Fink

187
00:12:17,667 --> 00:12:19,082
just like it's killed
everybody else.

188
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:20,541
What more proof do you need?

189
00:12:20,542 --> 00:12:22,082
Yeah, I'm with Mum on this one.
Forget the gold.

190
00:12:22,083 --> 00:12:24,332
Let somebody else feel
the weight of it.

191
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:25,832
We hit Jones
at this exchange instead.

192
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:28,042
Let him do the work for us.
We go for money.

193
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,666
I like where you're going
with this, son.

194
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:35,249
We cut the middleman,
play the end game.

195
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:37,166
What do you reckon, Lil?

196
00:12:37,167 --> 00:12:39,166
Decamp to the lockup?

197
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:42,832
Plan it out properly,
just like old times?

198
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:44,166
We pull this off, Mum,
and we're clear

199
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:46,291
of all this shit.

200
00:12:46,292 --> 00:12:48,666
We make for the sun
like you and Dad always wanted.

201
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:50,292
A new life away from all this.

202
00:13:55,083 --> 00:13:57,542
- Dad, you all right?
- Vic?

203
00:13:58,542 --> 00:13:59,666
Vic?

204
00:13:59,667 --> 00:14:01,166
<i>Don't shoot!</i>

205
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:02,374
<i>Dirty son of a bitch!</i>

206
00:14:02,375 --> 00:14:03,832
Vic?

207
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,666
Yeah, I'm all right.

208
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:09,457
Time to lay
these ghosts to rest.

209
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:11,083
Yeah.

210
00:14:24,292 --> 00:14:26,666
Girls?

211
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:27,875
Follow me.

212
00:14:35,042 --> 00:14:37,833
All right, Vic,
where's the work tools?

213
00:14:45,458 --> 00:14:46,667
Ma'am.

214
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:50,333
Do the honors, Hate 'Em.

215
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,417
Be rude not to, Vic.

216
00:15:15,667 --> 00:15:17,250
Albert?

217
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:23,457
Jesus, Dad,
I thought you was a bank robber,

218
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:24,832
not an urban guerrilla.

219
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:25,999
You know
I've always been a sucker

220
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,499
for big-boys' toys, Albert.

221
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,708
Hot potato!

222
00:15:49,125 --> 00:15:53,416
"Elm Lodge residence,
Chief Superintendent Jones."

223
00:15:53,417 --> 00:15:55,541
What you got?

224
00:15:55,542 --> 00:15:57,582
Maps. Aerial shots.

225
00:15:57,583 --> 00:16:00,582
Even some interior photos.

226
00:16:00,583 --> 00:16:02,582
We need plans
of the internal layout.

227
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:03,832
Building specs.

228
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:05,499
Looks like a modern house,

229
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:08,291
so, architectural records
should be available, right?

230
00:16:08,292 --> 00:16:09,458
Let's find out.

231
00:16:29,667 --> 00:16:31,167
- You all right under there?
- Yeah.

232
00:16:33,083 --> 00:16:35,082
Here we go.

233
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:36,499
Got it?

234
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:37,917
- You got it?
- Yeah.

235
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:41,249
Jesus.

236
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:43,166
Now that is
some old-school shit.

237
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:45,541
There is no school like
the old school, son.

238
00:16:45,542 --> 00:16:46,874
Ain't that the truth.

239
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:48,499
Can someone let me out now,
please?

240
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,167
Coming on out you come. Coming.

241
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:53,625
Ooh.

242
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,916
You all right?

243
00:16:56,917 --> 00:16:58,625
I ain't got time to bleed,
Hate 'em?

244
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:07,708
Hello, old girl. Been a while.

245
00:17:09,125 --> 00:17:10,624
Jesus, shouldn't that thing
be in a museum?

246
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:12,707
This thing's Old Gerty, son.

247
00:17:12,708 --> 00:17:15,332
Don't be fooled by her oil leaks
and rusty drawers.

248
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:18,667
This darling has tapped
more conflabs than MI5.

249
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,499
It's dead as a doornail, Vic.

250
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:24,916
Lift her up, Norm.

251
00:17:24,917 --> 00:17:26,250
Let's have a look.

252
00:17:34,042 --> 00:17:35,833
I'll get this old bird
singing in no time.

253
00:17:37,417 --> 00:17:39,999
That's everything we got
on Elm Lodge.

254
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,999
Blimey.
Honks a bit in here, Mr. Hill.

255
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,457
Yeah, well, you'd be a bit musty

256
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:46,207
if you've been banged up
for 15 years, Charlie.

257
00:17:46,208 --> 00:17:49,541
You think these Young Turks
are taking the mickey out of us?

258
00:17:49,542 --> 00:17:51,416
Would you like me to put them
in the Judas cradle, Victor?

259
00:17:51,417 --> 00:17:53,582
No, no, no, today we're all
love and light, Hate 'Em.

260
